Hybrid Physical Digital Storytelling Systems 















We’re creating physical, tangible, installation-based interactive storytelling systems to explore new design spaces for entertainment, intergenerational communication, and learning.Associated ProjectsMagia Transformo – The Dance of Transformation.The Reading GloveGeoPoetryRestless: The Haunted DollhouseUntitled Rangoli ProjectPhylacteryPensieve Box Associated Publications2010 Augmented Human Paper: The Reading Glove: Designing Interactions for Object-Based Tangible Storytelling2010 INT6 Paper: Authoring Tangible Interactive Narratives using Cognitive Hyperlinks2011 The Journal of the International Digital Media Art Association Article: Getting your hands on electronic literature: exploring tactile fictions with the Reading Glove2011 UMAP Paper: User Perceptions of Adaptivity in an Interactive Narrative2011 ICIDS Paper: The Reading Glove: a non-linear adaptive tangible narrative2011 TEI Paper: Experiencing the Reading Glove2014 User Modeling and User Adapted Interaction Article: A Case Study of Intended Versus Actual Experience of Adaptivity in a Tangible Storytelling System2016 ICIDS Paper: GeoPoetry: Designing Location-Based Combinatorial Electronic Literature Soundtracks for Roadtrips2016 ICIDS Paper: Phylactery: An Authoring Platform for Object Stories2016 iConference Paper: Penseive Box: Designing Tangible Platforms for Digital Memorialization Practices2016 TEI Paper: Penseive Box: Themes for Digital Memorialization Practices 


















